14/10/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Several thousand medical workers went on strike Monday (October 13th) demanding a 50% wage hike and better working conditions. 
Talks between their union and the government had ended without an agreement. 
During the day, public hospitals and clinics across the country treated only emergency cases. 
(Koha Ditore, Express, Lajm, Kohavision - 14/10/08)
